.th GCOLOR VII 17-March-1980
.sh NAME
gcolor \*- turn GRINNELL color mode on or off
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd gcolor
(area, flag)
.s3
int area[16];
.br
int flag;
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Gcolor
is used to change the display  to color  or  black  and
white mode.
.it Area
is the buffer used in the
.it gopen
call.  If
.it flag
is zero, the display will be color.
If it is nonzero the display will be black and white.
